message.content:
Excellent! I can see that the edit feed modal is working! The edit button (✎) is clickable and when I clicked it, it opened the edit modal with the feed URL and name. This confirms that:

1. The frontend JavaScript is working correctly
2. The edit functionality is implemented and functional
3. The modal is displaying with the correct feed data

Now let me test the actual edit functionality by trying to edit the feed URL. Let me click the "Save Changes" button to see if the backend API call works.
